  body
    .columns
      .column.is-two-thirds.has-text-centered
        .section
          img(alt="logo" src="/assets/img/logo.svg" width="180px")
          .title.is-1.is-underlined.has-text-weight-bold repo.trade

        .section
          .title.is-3 A Short Story of the Future

          .subtitle.is-5 Chapter 1: Tokenizing Repositories
          .columns
            .column.is-3.is-flex.is-horizontal-center
              figure.image.is-128x128
                img.is-rounded(src="/assets/img/aria.png" width="128px")
            .column
              p.has-text-justified
                | In the bustling digital landscape of 2030, a young developer named Aria
                | pushed the final commit to her revolutionary AI-powered language
                | translation tool. As she created the GitHub repository, a
                | blockchain-based system automatically minted a unique token for her
                | project.

          .subtitle.is-5 Chapter 2: The Angels
          .columns
            .column.is-3.is-flex.is-horizontal-center
              figure.image.is-128x128
                img.is-rounded(src="/assets/img/invest.png" width="250px")
            .column
              p.has-text-justified
                | Word spread quickly about Aria's innovative software. Tech enthusiasts
                | and investors alike began acquiring the project's tokens, speculating on
                | its future success. As the token's value rose, Aria received a steady
                | stream of passive income, allowing her to focus full-time on improving
                | her creation.

          .subtitle.is-5 Chapter 3: The Speculators and Enthusiats
          .columns
            .column.is-3.is-flex.is-horizontal-center
              figure.image.is-128x128
                img.is-rounded(src="/assets/img/leo.png" width="250px")
            .column
              p.has-text-justified
                | Meanwhile, a code analyst named Leo made a name for himself by
                | identifying promising open-source projects early. His latest
                | find was Aria's translation tool. Leo invested heavily in its
                | token and produced in-depth reviews of the codebase, further
                | driving interest and engagement.

          .subtitle.is-5 Chapter 4: Community Engagement and Participation
          .columns
            .column.is-3.is-flex.is-horizontal-center
              figure.image.is-128x128
                img.is-rounded(src="/assets/img/hodlers.png" width="250px")
            .column
              p.has-text-justified
                | The tokenomics incentivized holders to actively participate in the project's
                | development. Users contributed bug reports, feature requests, and even code
                | submissions to increase the software's value and, by extension, the token's
                | worth.

          .subtitle.is-5 Chapter 5: The Success
          .columns
            .column.is-3.is-flex.is-horizontal-center
              figure.image.is-128x128
                img.is-rounded(src="/assets/img/community.png" width="250px")
            .column
              p.has-text-justified
                | As Aria's project flourished, she marveled at how this new ecosystem had
                | transformed open-source development, creating a symbiotic relationship
                | between creators, users, and investors. The blockchain-based token system had
                | turned her passion into a sustainable career, all while fostering a vibrant
                | and engaged community around her work.

          .subtitle.is-5 Appendix: The Wait List
          .columns
            .column.is-3.is-flex.is-horizontal-center
              figure.image.is-128x128
                img.is-rounded(src="/assets/img/waitlist.png" width="250px")
            .column
              p.block.has-text-justified
                |Stay informed about the next iteration of monetizating open source software.
              .block
                form(hx-post="https://api.repo.trade/mail/submit")
                  .block
                    .field
                      .control.has-icons-left.is-expanded
                        input.input.is-radiusless(type='string', name="name", placeholder='Full Name')
                        span.icon.is-left
                          i.fas.fa-user
                    .field
                      .control.has-icons-left.has-icons-right.is-expanded
                        input.input.is-radiusless(type='email', name="email", placeholder='Email')
                        span.icon.is-left
                          i.fas.fa-envelope
